HEADWORD: Come-outer
<hw>Come-out"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who comes out
or withdraws from a religious or other organization; a radical
reformer.</def> <mark>[Colloq. U. S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

